<TITLE> Countrywide HSC exams begin </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 1 (bdnews24.com)-- The Higher Secondary Certificate and equivalent examinations began across the country on Thursday under 10 education boards. A total of 736,373 candidates sat for the Bangla 1st part exams on the first day. The examination started at 10am. Education minister Nurul Islam Nahid at a press conference on Tuesday warned teachers assigned to invigilation duty that if they were found helping students in unfair means, they would lose their jobs. He asked all to keep the exam centres free from cheating. Of the toal candidates, some 400,0464 are male and 335, 909 are female. Some 146 candidates are taking the exams from abroad at five centres in Jedda, Riad, Qatar, Abu Dhabi and Tripoli. 
